        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter">
                    <ab><title>Numbers 19</title>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                        <l><emph>Parashat Chukat</emph></l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                        <l n="1">And the Lord spoke to Moses
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             and to Aaron, saying,</l>
                        <l n="2">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             ‘This is the statute of the Law which the Lord has commanded, saying,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             “Speak to the children of Israel, that they bring you an unblemished
                            red
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             heifer, wherein is no blemish, and on which never came
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             a yoke.</l>
                        <l n="3">And you shall give it
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             to Eleazar, the priest, that he may bring it out outside the camp,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             and one shall slay it before him.</l>
                        <l n="4">And Eleazar the priest shall take
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             of its blood with his finger and sprinkle its blood toward
                            <milestone unit="page" n="245v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             the front of the tent of meeting seven times.</l>
                        <l n="5">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             And one shall burn the heifer in his sight: its skin,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             and its flesh, and its blood, with its
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             dung shall he burn it.</l>
                        <l n="6">And the priest shall take
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             cedar wood and hyssop and scarlet silk, and cast it
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             into the midst of the burning of the heifer.</l>
                        <l n="7">And the priest shall wash
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             his clothes and he shall wash his body with water, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             afterward he shall come to the camp. And the priest shall be unclean
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             until the evening.</l>
                        <l n="8">And the one who burns
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             it shall wash his clothes with water and wash
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             his body with water and he shall be unclean until the evening.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                        <l n="9">And a man that is clean shall gather up the ashes of the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             heifer and lay them up outside the camp in a clean place,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             and it shall be kept for the congregation of the children of Israel
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             for a purifying water: it is a sin offering.</l>
                        <l n="10">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             the one who gathers the ashes of the heifer shall wash his clothes,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             and he shall be unclean until the evening. And it shall be
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             for the children of Israel and for the stranger that lives
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             among them as an eternal statute.</l>
                        <l n="11">One
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             who touches the dead body of any human soul: then he shall be unclean
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             seven days.</l>
                        <l n="12">He shall purify himself with it on the
                            <milestone unit="page" n="246r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             third day, and on the <delSpan spanTo="#Num-019-del001_trl"
                                 />fourth<anchor type="delSpan" xml:id="Num-019-del001_trl" />
                            seventh day he shall be clean.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             And if he does not purify himself the third day, then
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             the seventh day he will not become clean.</l>
                        <l n="13">Anyone who touches
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             the dead body of any human soul who has died and does not purify
                            himself
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             defiles the tabernacle of the Lord, and that soul shall be cut off
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             from Israel. Because the purifying water was not sprinkled on him,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             he shall be unclean. His uncleanness is still in him.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                        <l n="14">This is the teaching: if a man dies in a tent,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             all who come into the tent and everything that is in the tent
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             shall be unclean seven days.</l>
                        <l n="15">And every open
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             vessel which has no covering fastened on it: it is unclean.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                        <l n="16">And anyone who, at an open field, touches
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             a killed body slain by a sword or a dead body or
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             a bone of a man or a grave shall be unclean
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             seven days.</l>
                        <l n="17">And they shall take
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             for an unclean person some of the ashes of the sin offering,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             and one shall put running water on it in a vessel.</l>
                        <l n="18">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             And a clean person shall take hyssop and dip it in the water and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             sprinkle it on the tent and on all the vessels
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             and on the souls that were
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             there and on the one who touched a bone or
                            <milestone unit="page" n="246v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             one slain or a dead or a grave.</l>
                        <l n="19">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             And the clean person shall make the unclean sprinkled
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             on the third day and on the seventh day. And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             on the seventh day he shall purify him and wash his clothes
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             and wash himself with water, and he shall be clean at evening.</l>
                        <l n="20">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             And if a man is unclean and he does not purify himself, then
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             that soul shall be cut off from among the assembly, because he has
                            defiled the sanctuary of the Lord.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             The purifying water has not been sprinkled on him:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             he is unclean.</l>
                        <l n="21">And it shall be an eternal
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             statute for them. And one who sprinkles the purifying water shall wash
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             his clothes, and one who touches the purifying water
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             shall be unclean until evening.</l>
                        <l n="22">And whatever the unclean person touches
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             shall be unclean, and any soul that touches |it|
                            <milestone unit="line" xml:id="Num019-P246v-L14_trl" n="14"
                                next="ADub.III.73.004.020.trl.xml#Num020-P246v-L14_trl" />
                             shall be unclean until evening.’ </l>
                    </ab>
